HEADWORD: Strelitzia
<hw>Stre*litz"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., named
after Charlotte, Princess of Mecklenburg-<etsep>Strelitz</etsep>, and
queen of George III of Great Britain.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of plants related to the banana, found at the Cape of Good Hope.
They have rigid glaucous distichous leaves, and peculiar richly colored
flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strene</ent>⟦br⟧
